eligibility_criteria.description:
Minimum age: 0 Years
Maximum age: 80 Years
This trial does not accept healthy volunteers.
Major surgery within 30 days prior to registration

Left ventricular ejection fraction (LVEF) that is at or above the lower institutional limits of normal, as assessed by multiple gated acquisition (MUGA) scan or echocardiogram within the 6 weeks prior to registration
Have chosen a radical prostatectomy for treatment of their disease after the medical team has presented all possible treatment options
Subjects requiring systemic corticosteroids (unless patient has had NO STEROIDS IN THE PAST 4 WEEKS)

Men who partner with a woman of childbearing potential, unless they agree to use
             effective contraception while on study drug.
The subject is unable or unwilling to stop taking vitamins, herbal remedies, or nonprescription medications
Had received a hematopoietic stem cell transplant (HSCT) within the previous 90 days

groups.description: Patients receive cyclophosphamide IV followed by anti-mesothelin iCasp9M28z CAR-transduced autologous T lymphocytes IV over 15-120 minutes 2 to 7 days later.

interventions.name: Anti-mesothelin iCasp9M28z CAR-transduced Autologous T Lymphocytes
Drug, Food, Chemical or Biomedical Material
Drug, Food, Chemical or Biomedical Material

groups.name: Treatment (cyclophosphamide, mesothelin-targeted T-cells)

outcome_measures.analysis_method: Regimen-related toxicity will be graded according to the National Cancer Institute (NCI) Common Terminology Criteria for Adverse Events (CTCAE).
outcome_measures.measure: Dose of melphalan required for the establishment of peripheral T cell tolerance with concomitant immune reconstitution and acceptable regimen related toxicity (Phase I)

outcome_measures.analysis_method: Will explore whether knowledge-based planning (KBP) can improve IG-IMRT plans compared to plans that would have been delivered without KBP, estimate the resulting toxicity reduction using normal tissue complication probability (NTCP) models, and determine whether KBP should be a requirement for future IG-IMRT protocols
outcome_measures.measure: Type of intensity modulated radiation therapy (IG-IMRT)

outcome_measures.analysis_method: A summary of adverse events will be tabulated at baseline and during treatment. Adverse event summaries will be organized by body system, frequency of occurrence, intensity (i.e., severity grade), and causality or attribution. Patients who experience an adverse event more than once will be counted only once. The occurrence with the maximum severity will be used to calculate intensity.
outcome_measures.measure: Incidence of long term toxicity to treatment using the NCI CTCAE v4.0

outcome_measures.analysis_method: Progression, for those patients with no decline in PSA from baseline, is defined as an increase in PSA that is >= 25% and >= 2 ng/mL after 12 weeks. Note: PSA progression as such will not lead to study discontinuation.
outcome_measures.measure: Progression, for those patients with no decline in PSA from baseline
